      • getInvokedObjSet

        static Set<Object> getInvokedObjSet(Object object,
                                    String regExStartsWith,
                                    String regExEndsWith)
                             throws org.openbase.jul.exception.CouldNotPerformException
        Method returns an invoked method set, which are matching with the regular expressions.
        Parameters:
        object - The class object, which contains the method(s) and data.
        regExStartsWith - Beginning expression part of the method name. Is set to lowercase.
        regExEndsWith - Ending expression part of the method name. Is set to lowercase.
        Returns:
        Set of invoked objects.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.CouldNotPerformException - Exception is thrown, if the identified methods could not be invoked, cause of wrong parameters or missing regex match.

      • getMethodSetByRegEx

        static Set<Method> getMethodSetByRegEx(Class<?> dataClass,
                                       String regExStartsWith,
                                       String regExEndsWith)
                                throws org.openbase.jul.exception.CouldNotPerformException
        Method returns a set of method(s) of a dataClass. The set of methodObject(s) is selected by matches with the delivered regular expressions.
        Parameters:
        dataClass - The class data, which contains the method(s).
        regExStartsWith - Beginning expression part of the method name. Method sets to lowercase.
        regExEndsWith - Ending expression part of the method name. Method sets to lowercase.
        Returns:
        Set of methods.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.CouldNotPerformException - Exception is thrown, if methods could not be find, because of null parameter or there is no method with matching name.
